{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"passed down to each subview.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ItemView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" may be added and removed at different times the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/text\/geometrygroup()"]}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE13geometryGroupQryF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore4TextV","title":"geometryGroup()","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"}],"role":"symbol","platforms":[{"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"10.15","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"6.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false}],"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"remoteSource":{"fileName":"RendererEffect.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Render\/RendererEffect\/RendererEffect.swift#L294"},"roleHeading":"Instance Method"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text\/geometryGroup()"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Text":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Text","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/text","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Text","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Text","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","abstract":[]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","type":"topic","title":"OpenSwiftUI","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for your app on every platform."}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Text/geometryGroup()":{"title":"geometryGroup()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text\/geometryGroup()","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/text\/geometrygroup()","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"View","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that represents part of your app’s user interface and provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifiers that you use to configure views."}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","role":"symbol"}}}